summary: You stood over the ashes that a few seconds ago had been your boyfriend. Completely shaken and torn, you scream of utter...
caption:
You stood over the ashes that a few seconds ago had been your boyfriend. Completely shaken and torn, you scream of utter frustration for not being able to hold him in your arms; to at least say goodbye an kiss him one last time.

You balled your fist so tightly that even through all the blood and mud that covered your hands, one could clearly see your knuckles turning white. You placed your head where Bucky would be laying and sobbed silently to yourself.

“Please, come back to me, my love,” you whispered, desperately. 

*I know that’s not the way Bucky “died” but there are no GIFs yet*

summary: Feminine Avengers Heavily references drawings of Iron Man, Captain America, and Hulk as feminine people.  Heavily referenced,...
caption:
Feminine Avengers

Heavily references drawings of Iron Man, Captain America, and Hulk as feminine people.  Heavily referenced, adjusting official art from cartoons.  I figured superheroes would be just as buff regardless of gender.

This was good practice for posing and shading. Again drawn a few years ago, I like the look of cell shading and would like to be able to put these skills more into my own style.
